---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Christoffer Oxenius"
  description="A decade building and scaling GTM, marketing, growth, and product across B2B SaaS, FinTech, and e-commerce."
  theme="light"
>
  <div class="home-shell">
    <section class="about-split">
      <div class="about-split-text">
        <h1>Christoffer Oxenius</h1>
        <p>
          Christoffer Oxenius (formerly Pettersson) is currently the CPO at <a href="https://njord.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Njord</a>,
          building an AI-native operating system for complex sales.
        </p>
        <p>
          He has spent the last decade building and scaling GTM, marketing,
          growth, and product across B2B SaaS, FinTech, and e-commerce, and
          is regarded as one of the leading B2B marketers in Sweden.
        </p>
        <p>
          He was the first full-time employee and later CMO at <a href="https://www.cnbc.com/2024/10/01/mastercard-to-buy-subscription-management-startup-minna-technologies.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Minna Technologies</a>, where he
          helped grow the company from an early Swedish startup to a global
          SaaS FinTech, from seed to Series B, and to around 80 people before
          it was later acquired by Mastercard.<span class="bio-toggle"> <span class="bio-toggle-ellipsis">…</span> <a href="#" class="bio-toggle-link">More</a></span>
        </p>
        <p class="bio-extra" hidden>
          Since then, he has served as CPO at <a href="https://www.megadeals.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Megadeals</a>, helping grow ARR from
          1M to 20M+ SEK in 12 months by co-building the offer, GTM strategy,
          and demand engine, and as Head of Growth at <a href="https://www.di.se/digital/mjukvarubolaget-efter-kundrusningen-aggressiva-tillvaxtmal/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sysarb</a> during a year when
          ARR grew from approximately 35M to 55M SEK and inbound booked
          meetings increased 5x.
        </p>
        <p class="bio-extra" hidden>
          He has also worked as CMO at <a href="https://www.breakit.se/artikel/35657/devotion-ska-satsa-pa-hundratals-saas-bolag-och-har-en-plan-for-att-gora-kvalitet-av-kvantitet" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Devotion Ventures</a>, leading
          fractional CMO engagements across 10+ VC portfolio companies, helped
          scale <a href="https://www.breakit.se/artikel/33185/mardrommen-for-spotify-storytel-och-netflix-anyfin-och-minna-technologies-gar-ihop-for-att-doda-abonnemangen" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Mina Tjänster</a> from 5,000 to 500,000 users, and built an <a href="https://www.instagram.com/karlexwatches/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">e-commerce brand</a> from
          0 to approximately 2M SEK during university.
        </p>
        <p class="bio-extra" hidden>
          He holds a Master's degree in Marketing from Gothenburg School of
          Business, and a Bachelor's degree in Marketing from Luleå University
          of Technology.
        </p>
        <p class="bio-extra" hidden>
          Christoffer is regarded as one of the leading B2B marketers in Sweden.
          He has been interviewed by <a href="https://tonyhammarlund.io/christoffer-pettersson-12/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Tony Hammarlund</a>, <a href="https://music.amazon.com.mx/podcasts/a922aa1b-a740-46f1-aaf0-c833b23a9af4/episodes/8539a2eb-abab-446c-aea2-1250a5afb187/the-breakout-growth-podcast-minna-technologies-cmo-christoffer-pettersson-explains-the-advantages-of-starting-b2c-and-then-pivoting-to-b2b" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Sean Ellis</a>
          (author of <em>Hacking Growth</em>), the <a href="https://open.spotify.com/episode/3cq5nIJ3ko43SsTNwrofOQ" target="_blank" rel="noopener">11:FS FinTech Marketing Podcast</a>,
          and <a href="https://medium.com/@rebelandbird/s%C3%A5-sprider-du-insikter-fr%C3%A5n-experimenti-avsnitt-4-av-growthpodden-ges-konkreta-tips-p%C3%A5-hur-du-50ba07ea4f13" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Growthpodden</a>,
          and has guest blogged on <a href="https://www.11fs.com/article/what-does-effective-growth-marketing-look-like-for-b2b-in-the-2020s" target="_blank" rel="noopener">11:FS</a>.
          He is also an active thought leader on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/christofferoxenius/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>, with over
          10,000 followers.
        </p>
        <p class="bio-extra" hidden>
          He writes and talks about B2B GTM, positioning, AI operations, and
          what actually moves pipeline.
        </p>
        <h2 class="home-list-title">Thinking &amp; Writing</h2>
        <ul class="home-list">
          <li><a href="/blog-posts">Blog posts</a></li>
          <li><a href="/essays">Essays</a></li>
          <li><a href="/playbooks">Playbooks</a></li>
          <li><a href="/tech-stack">Tech stack</a></li>
          <li><a href="/bookmarks">Bookmarks</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <figure class="about-split-image">
        <img
          src="/portrait.jpg"
          alt="Christoffer Oxenius"
          loading="eager"
        />
      </figure>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<script>
  const link = document.querySelector<HTMLAnchorElement>('.bio-toggle-link');
  const ellipsis = document.querySelector<HTMLElement>('.bio-toggle-ellipsis');
  const extras = document.querySelectorAll<HTMLElement>('.bio-extra');

  link?.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    const expanded = link.textContent === 'Less';
    extras.forEach((p) => {
      p.hidden = expanded;
    });
    link.textContent = expanded ? 'More' : 'Less';
    if (ellipsis) {
      ellipsis.style.display = expanded ? '' : 'none';
    }
  });
</script>
